@startuml
!include ../style.puml

title Read Restart In Module 05

' [step1 {"name":"Module 04 can miss a recent commit"}]
actor "Reader txn" as reader
participant "Storage replica" as replica
database "Committed MVCC versions" as store

reader -> replica: TxnRead(key=account-101,\nreadTs=(1000,0))
activate replica
replica -> store: get committed versions\n<= readTs
store --> replica: no visible version at 1000
replica --> reader: found=false
deactivate replica

note right of reader
In module 04 this read can miss
a value committed just after 1000
but still inside the uncertainty window.
end note
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Module 05 checks the uncertainty window"}]
reader -> replica: TxnRead(key=account-101,\nreadTs=(1000,0))
activate replica
replica -> replica: uncertaintyLimit = readTs + maxOffset
replica -> store: inspect versions up to uncertaintyLimit
store --> replica: latest committed version at (1005,0)
replica --> reader: error=Read restart required,\npropagatedTime=(1005,0)
deactivate replica
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Client restarts at a safe timestamp"}]
reader -> reader: move snapshot forward\nrestart read at (1005,0)
reader -> replica: TxnRead(key=account-101,\nreadTs=(1005,0))
activate replica
replica -> store: get committed versions\n<= (1005,0)
store --> replica: value=1000
replica --> reader: found=true, value=1000
deactivate replica

note bottom
The write path stays fast.
Only the unlucky read inside the uncertainty window restarts.
end note
' [/step3]

@enduml
